e of thumb is do not make\r\n       any assumption about whether a path belongs to $GIT_DIR or $GIT_COMMON_DIR when you\r\n       need to directly access something inside $GIT_DIR. Use git rev-parse --git-path to\r\n       get the final path.\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe better stick to that strategy.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3529/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/3529/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}